President Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated Sir Kensington Adebukunola Adebutu on the conferment of the title ‘‘Odole –Oodua’’ October 19, 2019, by His Imperial Majesty, Ooni Adeyeye Enitan Ogunwusi, Arole Oodua – Ojaja II. The President, according to a statement by the Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Chief Femi Adesina, felicitated with family members, friends and business associates of Sir Adebutu for the title which was held in the past by Chief Obafemi Awolowo. He urged him to keep up the good work that heralded such a worthy recognition. President Buhari also greeted wives of the businessman, Dame Caroline Oladunni Adebutu and Yeye Kofoworola Adebutu, who are also conferred with titles, “Yeyemode-Oodua’’ and “Yeyerewa-Oodua,’’ respectively.